NEW AMSTERDAM CASUALTY COMPANY, v. K. SUGAYA. No. 7976. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 14, 1935. Hadsell, Sweet, Ingalls & Lamb and Joe G. Sweet, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. James F. Brennan, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered, appeal dismissed, without costs; that sureties on undertaking on appeal be discharged from liability ; mandate forthwith.
